		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Cloud seeding</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Cloud seeding</b>, a form of <a href="/wiki/Weather_control" title="Weather control">weather modification</a>, is the attempt to change the amount or type of <a href="/wiki/Precipitation_(meteorology)" title="Precipitation (meteorology)">precipitation</a> that falls from <a href="/wiki/Cloud" title="Cloud">clouds</a>, by dispersing substances into the <a href="/wiki/Air" title="Air" class="mw-redirect">air</a> that serve as <a href="/wiki/Cloud_condensation_nuclei" title="Cloud condensation nuclei">cloud condensation</a> or <a href="/wiki/Ice_nucleus" title="Ice nucleus">ice nuclei</a>, which alter the microphysical processes within the cloud. The usual intent is to increase precipitation (rain or snow), but hail and fog suppression are also widely practiced in airports.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
<tr>
<td>
